Everything `zig build` needs at runtime on plan9: std.process.Child
spawnPlan9 (rfork+exec+pipes, no CLOEXEC/errpipe), std.io pollPlan9
(blocking-read poller — no poll(2)), Progress have_ipc=false, Watch.init
runtime-fails on void-Os OSes, the build runner's fuzz/std.net block
comptime-gated, Options/Run cross-directory moves, Target.zig's
stage2_x86_64 vector workarounds extended to plan9, and main.zig: the
Cc9Allocator (cc9-malloc-backed gpa with REAL free — magic-validated
stash headers convert any wild/corrupted free into a logged, leaked block
with an rbp backtrace instead of a GP fault) and cmdBuild forcing the
runner to ReleaseSmall+single-threaded+strip on plan9.

